The paper deals with algorithms for computing minimum-cost maximum cardinality matchings in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on minor-free graphs, which are a well-studied class of graphs with many interesting properties. The paper uses techniques from graph theory, combinatorics, and algorithm design and analysis. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
